<subSubSection box="[113,886,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,266,931]" box="[113,886,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,261,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<typeStatus box="[113,169,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel, 1913" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1913" box="[268,701,266,290]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Parallelomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[268,548,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Parallelomma longicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="HENDEL F." box="[555,701,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="77 - 112" refId="ref2514" refString="HENDEL F. 1913: Acalyptrate Musciden (Dipt.) II. Entomologische Mitteilungen, Supplementa Entomologica 2: 77 - 112." type="journal article" year="1913">Hendel, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, here designated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="290" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,266,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,223,298,322]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The main diagnostic characters are as follows: anterior third of frons arcuatelly receding in both sexes (in lateral view), genae with one strong and long bristle, palpi without long apical bristle, one katepisternal bristle, fore femora with one distinct, short spine-like bristle interiorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,266,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,365,426,450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Šifner, 2009" authorityName="Šifner" authorityYear="2009" box="[372,451,427,450]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Suwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[372,451,427,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Suwaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[458,556,427,451]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs distinctly from other related genera in the following characters: i) anterior third of frons strongly arcuately receding in both sexes; ii) arista very sparsely plumose, palpi rectangular, very narrowed basally, in proximal half enlarged and apically rounded with four black bristles; iii) fore femora with one distinct bristle interiorly; iv) epiphallus short with lateral plates, from basal part of distiphallus prolate with two lateral membraneous lobes (
<figureCitation box="[456,559,586,610]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1048,1067]" captionTargetBox="[153,1124,222,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-169@4.[151,1126,219,1017]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 5–9. Suwaia longicornis (Hendel, 1913). 5–8 – J paratype: 5 – abdominal sternites 4 to 5; 6 – cerci and surstyli (caudal view); 7 – pregonite and postgonite (lateral view); 8 – epiphallus, pregonites, postgonites and lateral membraneous lobes (dorsal view). 9 – ♀ paratype, abdominal stenites 6 to 8 (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 5–6, 9), 0.1 mm (Figs. 7–8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319125/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
); and v) sternite 8 narrow without bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1076,586,610]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1048,1067]" captionTargetBox="[153,1124,222,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-169@4.[151,1126,219,1017]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 5–9. Suwaia longicornis (Hendel, 1913). 5–8 – J paratype: 5 – abdominal sternites 4 to 5; 6 – cerci and surstyli (caudal view); 7 – pregonite and postgonite (lateral view); 8 – epiphallus, pregonites, postgonites and lateral membraneous lobes (dorsal view). 9 – ♀ paratype, abdominal stenites 6 to 8 (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 5–6, 9), 0.1 mm (Figs. 7–8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319125/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Other key diagnostic characters, i.e., long apical bristle on the palpus, the shape of surstylus and the shape of female abdominal sternites are entirely different in both 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1894" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Parallelomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1089,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Parallelomma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BECKER T." box="[113,254,682,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="77 - 196" refId="ref2465" refString="BECKER T. 1894: Dipterologische Studien. I. Scatomyzidae. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 39: 77 - 196." type="journal article" year="1894">Becker, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1894" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[306,615,682,706]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Megaphthalma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[306,467,683,706]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Megaphthalma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BECKER T." box="[474,615,682,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="77 - 196" refId="ref2465" refString="BECKER T. 1894: Dipterologische Studien. I. Scatomyzidae. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 39: 77 - 196." type="journal article" year="1894">Becker, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see Comments below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="290" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,266,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,240,714,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Etymology.</emphasis>
I dedicate this genus to the Japanese dipterist Maasaki Suwa (Hokkaido University Museum, Sapporo). The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,266,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,243,778,802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="HENDEL F." box="[249,408,778,802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="77 - 112" refId="ref2514" refString="HENDEL F. 1913: Acalyptrate Musciden (Dipt.) II. Entomologische Mitteilungen, Supplementa Entomologica 2: 77 - 112." type="journal article" year="1913">HENDEL (1913)</bibRefCitation>
described and classified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1913" box="[673,953,779,802]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Parallelomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[673,953,779,802]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Parallelomma longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[113,266,811,834]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Parallelomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,266,811,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Parallelomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="VOCKEROTH J. R." box="[320,520,810,834]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="436 - 438" refId="ref2820" refString="VOCKEROTH J. R. 1977: Superfamily Muscoidea, Family Scathophagidae. Pp. 436 - 438. In: DELFINADO M. D. &amp; HARDY D. E. (eds.): A catalog of the Diptera of the Oriental Region. Volume III. Suborder Cyclorrhapha (excluding division Aschiza). The University Press of Hawaii, Honolulu, 854 pp." type="book chapter" year="1977">VOCKEROTH (1977)</bibRefCitation>
placed it in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[768,929,811,834]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Megaphthalma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[768,929,811,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Megaphthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the species cannot be placed in either genus due to the combination of its diagnostic characters, including the newly recognized characters on male and female genitalia. Therefore, I establish for it a new genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Šifner, 2009" authorityName="Šifner" authorityYear="2009" box="[318,397,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Suwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[318,397,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Suwaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[403,500,907,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
